<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-14T21:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-14T21:41:00-05:00" n="1140" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1140">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/66.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Miller</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-14T20:00:00-06:41">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 14, 1914, 8 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Constitutionalist force under General Pablo Gonzalez occupied Tampico
                            yesterday about noon. Perfect order being preserved. Guaranties assured
                            to all foreigners to return to their business.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Miller</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>